Thailand Stocks: Bangkok Bank, Thoresen Thai, UOB Kay Hian

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-08-24T09:55:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-24/siam-commercial-bank-singer-thailand-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Thailand  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 4:30 p.m. close in Bangkok.  The SET Index fell for a fifth day, dropping 10.85 points,
or 1 percent, to 1,046.43.  Banks:  Bangkok Bank Pcl (BBL)  led declines in commercial lenders
on concern higher interest rates will curb new loans. Bangkok
Bank (BBL TB), Thailand’s biggest lender, declined 2.3 percent
to 151 baht.  Kasikornbank Pcl (KBANK)   lost 1.2 percent to
124.5 baht.  Siam Commercial Bank Pcl (SCB)   slipped 1.7
percent to 114.5 baht.  Thailand’s central bank today raised its benchmark  interest
rate  for the seventh meeting as the government’s plans to boost
wages and rice prices heighten inflation risks.  Thoresen Thai Agencies Pcl (TTA)  , Thailand’s second-
largest bulk shipping company, dropped 3.5 percent to 19.3 baht,
the most since Aug. 8. Thoresen expects the oversupply of
commodity transportation vessels will continue for the next two
or three years on the delivery of new carriers, Thitima
Rungkwansiriroj, the company’s chief financial officer, told
investors in Bangkok today.  UOB Kay Hian Securities (Thailand) Pcl (UOBKH TB), a stock
brokerage, jumped 7.7 percent to 3.92 baht, the largest increase
since Jan. 11. The company will offer investors 0.42 share for
each share held as a stock dividend, it said in a regulatory
filing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
 anguyen@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net . 